## Summary

I have successfully fixed the bug in Apache Commons CLI. Here's what I did:

### Problem Analysis
The bug was in `OptionGroup.java`. The test `BugCLI266Test::testOptionComparatorInsertedOrder` was failing because when options were added to an `OptionGroup`, their insertion order was not preserved. This happened because the `optionMap` field was using a `HashMap` which doesn't maintain insertion order.

### Solution
I changed the `HashMap` to a `LinkedHashMap` in the `OptionGroup` class to preserve the insertion order of options within an option group.

### Changes Made
1. Added import for `java.util.LinkedHashMap`
2. Changed the `optionMap` field from `HashMap<String, Option>` to `LinkedHashMap<String, Option>`

### Verification
- The triggering test `org.apache.commons.cli.bug.BugCLI266Test::testOptionComparatorInsertedOrder` now passes
- The related test `org.apache.commons.cli.bug.BugCLI266Test::testOptionComparatorDefaultOrder` also passes  
- All project tests pass, indicating no regression was introduced
- The fix maintains backward compatibility while ensuring options within an OptionGroup maintain their insertion order

### Patch Created
The patch is saved in `blind_fix.patch` with the following content:

```diff
diff --git a/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/cli/OptionGroup.java b/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/cli/OptionGroup.java
index 322053f..cec7ea2 100644
--- a/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/cli/OptionGroup.java
+++ b/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/cli/OptionGroup.java
@@ -21,6 +21,7 @@ import java.io.Serializable;
 import java.util.Collection;
 import java.util.HashMap;
 import java.util.Iterator;
+import java.util.LinkedHashMap;
 import java.util.Map;

 /**
@@ -34,7 +35,7 @@ public class OptionGroup implements Serializable
     private static final long serialVersionUID = 1L;

     /** hold the options */
-    private final Map<String, Option> optionMap = new HashMap<String, Option>();
+    private final Map<String, Option> optionMap = new LinkedHashMap<String, Option>();

     /** the name of the selected option */
     private String selected;
```

This change ensures that when options are retrieved from an OptionGroup using the `getOptions()` method, they are returned in the same order they were inserted, fixing the ordering issue in the bug test case.

